text: Thoisy may refer to: ==People== * Geoffroy de Thoisy, Burgundian naval commander involved in Philip the Good’s Crusade endeavors in the 1440s. * Noël Patrocles de Thoisy (died 1671), early governor general of the French Antilles ==Places== * Thoisy-la-Berchère, commune in the Côte-d'Or department in eastern France * Thoisy-le-Désert commune in the Côte-d'Or department in eastern France
title: Thoisy
